image.asymptote:
// 3-D interactive (WebGL) figure.
import graph3;
size(8.5cm);
currentprojection=orthographic(5,3,2.4);
real a=2;
path3 helix=graph(new triple(real t){return (a*cos(t), a*sin(t), t/3);}, 0, 3.5pi, 220, operator ..);
draw(helix, blue+linewidth(1.1pt));
draw(circle((0,0,0), a, (0,0,1)), gray(0.6)+dashed);
real t0=1.2; triple P=(a*cos(t0), a*sin(t0), t0/3);
triple v=(-a*sin(t0), a*cos(t0), 1.0/3);
dot(P); label("$P$", P, SW);
draw(P--(P+v), red+linewidth(1.3pt), Arrow3); label("$\mathbf r'(t)$", P+v, N);
draw(O--(3,0,0),gray,Arrow3); draw(O--(0,3,0),gray,Arrow3); draw(O--(0,0,4.2),gray,Arrow3);
label("$x$",(3,0,0),S); label("$y$",(0,3,0),E); label("$z$",(0,0,4.2),N);

subsection.p:
For motion, the theorem says:
\boxed{\int_a^b \mathbf v(t)\,dt=\mathbf r(b)-\mathbf r(a).}
The integral of velocity is displacement.
